The paper deals with the parameterized complexity of a graph problem, specifically the Minimum Changeover Cost Arborescence (MINCCA) problem. This problem involves finding an arborescence with minimum total changeover cost of internal vertices in an edge-colored graph. The paper focuses on the parameterized complexity of this problem, which suggests that it is likely to belong to categories such as cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), cs.CG (Computational Geometry), cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory), and cs.CC (Computational Complexity). These categories are all relevant to the study of graph problems and their complexity.
